liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: We have witnessed a fantastic opening ceremony at Eden Park in Auckland. The excitement is at fever pitch for the opening match between New Zealand and Norway.

children.content: The excitement is at fever pitch for the opening match between New Zealand and Norway.

props.alt: Men and women dressed in black and white sitting in grandstands.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: You'll be able to watch New Zealand face Norway at 5pm AEST on 7mate, its streaming service 7+ and Optus Sport. Later on, when our Matildas take on the Republic of Ireland at 8pm AEST, you'll be able to watch it on Channel 7, 7+ and Optus Sport. ABC Sport is broadcasting live, uninterrupted and commercial free coverage every day of the 2023 FIFA Women’s World Cup on the ABC listen app. And as always, we'll be bringing you all the latest here on the ABC Sport live blog.
